  "text": "Laramee et al. visualized flow properties of a cooling jacket, where the physical geometry plays an important role in flow [CITATION_1] . In addition to showing flow lines and semi-transparent rendering of the solid structure, they also displayed information on the geometry. Scalar values, such as temperature, were used in colormap rendering to denote areas of the cooling jacket with high temperature. They also applied imagespace advection to identify recirculation using geometry textures [CITATION_2] .",
